name: Casa Bhonsle Restaurant and Bar

reviews.review_text:
This is very old classic restaurant. You get variety of food options here. They had divided into two sections, top floor serves non veg and bottom one serves veg only. Last time I visited, non veg section was closed. I had tried their veg thali which was good. All the items in the plate tasted really well including the chutney which added a unique flavour. Rajma prepared did not played well with my taste palette. Quantity of the items are fulfilling. They serve you two rotis and rice which will make you full for sure.
Overall a good thali.

Not worth the price and hype. Tried the fish thali there. It's priced at 250 rupees and I was not quite satisfied with the quality of fish and the taste as well. The stars of a thali are the rice, curry and fish and I was not happy with either of them. I am guessing they add soda to the rice which kinda bloats you up after the meal.

Next time, I tried their chicken fried rice and chilli chicken. 250 for chilli chicken and 180 rupees for fried rice would be great to pay if it was extraordinarily good. But the taste here was as good as a local Street side Chinese shop.

So nope from my side.

Only Veg restuarant is open. Non Veg is closed for now. Tried out the Makkan Peda and Famous Punjabi Samosa. Great taste. ðŸ‘Œ

Edit: Tried out some items from their Lunch menu ie Veg Pulao(3/5) too much oily and felt like Fried rice, Gobi Dry, little bit overfried (4/5) and Veg thali(4/5).

### Casa Bhonsle Restaurant and Bar: A Culinary Voyage in Cavelossim, Goa

Nestled in the scenic locale of Cavelossim, Goa, **Casa Bhonsle Restaurant and Bar** has garnered a commendable rating of **4.2** from **2,127** patrons, highlighting its popularity and inviting ambiance. Revered for its **thalis**, **Goan delicacies**, and an array of **snacks**, this eatery promises a delightful culinary experience that reflects the rich flavors of local cuisine.

### Ambiance & Design

Casa Bhonsle exudes a classic charm with its divided layout: a vibrant top floor dedicated to non-vegetarian delights (currently closed during some visits) and a busy ground floor offering vegetarian options. The dÃ©cor offers a pleasant nod to traditional Goan aesthetics, harmonizing rustic elegance with comfort. Patrons often mention the inviting atmosphere, accentuated by warm lighting and subtle music that enhances the dining experience without overpowering conversation.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The restaurantâ€™s **menu** features an enticing selection, showcasing both vegetarian and non-vegetarian fare. Signature dishes such as the **veg thali** and **fish thali** have received mixed reviews. While one guest found the **veg thali** to be fulfilling and flavorfulâ€”highlighting its chutney that added a unique touchâ€”another noted that the **fish thali** fell short in quality and flavor, leading to disappointment despite its reasonable pricing. The restaurant further diverges into local favorites, presenting items like **Makkan Peda** and **Punjabi Samosa**, which received praises for their remarkable taste.

The thalis are generously portioned, ensuring diners leave satisfied. For those preferring lighter fare, the **Veg Pulao** and dishes like **Gobi Dry** add further variety; however, some feedback suggests these can occasionally verge on being too oily or overfried.

### Customer Experience & Service

The service at Casa Bhonsle receives accolades for its attentive and friendly staff. The restaurant operates on a walk-in basis, creating a laid-back dining environment that resonates with Goa's leisurely lifestyle. Guests appreciate the prompt service, which complements the relaxed ambiance, making it a fitting spot for a leisurely meal.

### Popularity & Reviews

Customer feedback paints a varied picture of experience at Casa Bhonsle, reflecting its ability to cater to a diverse audience. Social media buzz echoes a fondness for its thalis and local dishes, yet also addresses room for improvement in consistency, particularly with specific menu items. Despite the critiques, its overall favorable reviews emphasize the restaurant's status as a beloved local spot, with many vowing to return.

### Utilizing Visual Content

Images shared by patrons further illustrate the restaurantâ€™s appeal. The beautifully presented thalis, vibrant with colors and textures, are reminiscent of a home-cooked meal. The **Makkan Peda** and **Punjabi Samosa** photos showcase a tempting array that would entice any foodie. Such visuals reinforce Casa Bhonsle as not just a place to eat, but a sensory experience to savor.

In conclusion, **Casa Bhonsle Restaurant and Bar** embodies the essence of Goan dining with its rich flavors, warm atmosphere, and a menu laden with local favorites. While some dishes may leave room for improvement, the restaurantâ€™s commitment to quality and service ensures a memorable culinary journey that many find worthwhile.
